{
  "uuid": "3270e1b6a10920ac2fc2a82a6a005c5e",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Mechanical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1.\tCreate, modify, and maintain accurate 3D CAD models of mechanical components and      assemblies.</p><p>2.\tGenerate detailed 2D drawings, including dimensions, tolerances, surface finishes, and assembly instructions, ensuring compliance with company and industry standards.</p><p>3.\tDevelop and maintain Bills of Materials (BOMs) for all designed products, ensuring correct part numbering, revisions, and specifications.</p><p>4.\tPrepare, update, and maintain Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) and Work Instructions (WIs) related to mechanical design, assembly, and manufacturing processes.</p><p>5.\tSupport Engineering Change Requests (ECRs) and Engineering Change Orders (ECOs) by providing technical input, updating CAD models, drawings, BOMs, and related documentation.</p><p>6.\tAssist in assembly of full turnkey machines, including mechanical assembly, fitting, alignment, adjustment, and troubleshooting</p><p>7.\tProvide hands-on support during prototype builds and first articles</p><p>8.\tResolve assembly issues and implement design improvements quickly</p><p>9.\tDesign and develop jigs, fixtures, and assembly aids to support manufacturing and machine assembly</p><p>10.\tSupport continuous improvement initiatives on the shop floor</p><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><p>1.\tBachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent</p><p>2.\tMinimum of 2 years of experience in mechanical-related work and hands-on implementation in a manufacturing environment (preferred).</p><p>3.\tStrong practical skills in mechanical assembly and working with equipment</p><p>4.\tProficiency in 3D CAD software especially Solid Works</p><p>5.\tStrong understanding of mechanical components (bearings, actuators, gears, pneumatics, fasteners, etc.)</p><p>6.\tComfortable working hands-on in an assembly and manufacturing environment</p><p>7.\tFamiliarity with factory tooling/fixtures is a strong plus.</p><p>8.\tSelf-driven, detail-oriented, and able to work independently to resolve technical challenges.</p><p>9.\tOpen to work overtime if required.</p><p></p>",
